<subSubSection id="34F177A62E61EF7EFF54FB4AFEED7B33" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7C54242D2E61EF7EFF54FB4AFEED7B33" blockId="28.[189,1398,976,1306]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
This Atlantic species has the same English common name as 
<taxonomicName id="BBEB5FAE2E61EF7EFC27FB4BFBC37A93" authority="Brauer, 1906" authorityName="Brauer" authorityYear="1906" box="[897,1142,1186,1210]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Evermannellidae" genus="Evermannella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aulopiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E61EF7EFC27FB4BFC577A93" box="[897,994,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">E. indica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="187A59DC2E61EF7EFC4EFB4AFBC37A93" author="Brauer A." box="[1000,1142,1186,1210]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref38809" refString="Brauer A. 1906. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition auf dem Dampfer &quot; Valdivia &quot; 1898 - 1899. Jena, Naumburg." type="book" year="1906">Brauer, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. A revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BBEB5FAE2E61EF7EFF54FB2AFE3D7AF3" box="[242,392,1218,1242]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Evermannellidae" genus="Evermannella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aulopiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E61EF7EFF54FB2AFE3D7AF3" box="[242,392,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Evermannella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resulted in the distinction between the species (
<bibRefCitation id="187A59DC2E61EF7EFC26FB2AFBAA7AF3" author="Swinney G. N." box="[896,1055,1218,1242]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="809 - 819" refId="ref44417" refString="Swinney G. N. 1994. Comments on the Atlantic species of the genus Evermannella (Scopelomorpha, Aulopiformes, Evermannellidae) with a re-evaluation of the status of Evermanella melanoderma. Journal of Fish Biology 44: 809 - 819. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8649.1994. tb 01257. x" type="journal article" year="1994">Swinney 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, all previous records of 
<taxonomicName id="BBEB5FAE2E61EF7EFEB6FB0BFEC47AD3" authorityName="Brauer" authorityYear="1906" box="[272,369,1250,1274]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Evermannellidae" genus="Evermannella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aulopiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E61EF7EFEB6FB0BFEC47AD3" box="[272,369,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">E. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Atlantic are now known as 
<taxonomicName id="BBEB5FAE2E61EF7EFD43FB0BFC257AD3" box="[741,912,1250,1274]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Evermannellidae" genus="Evermannella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aulopiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanoderna">
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E61EF7EFD43FB0BFC257AD3" box="[741,912,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">E. melanoderna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="BBEB5FAE2E61EF7EFC38FB0AFC557AD0" box="[926,992,1250,1273]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Stomiidae" genus="Idiacanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stomiiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="our">In our</taxonomicName>
opinion the common name should be modified.
</paragraph>
